issue.title: Feature/df 18971 gsr lwba endpoint
issue.body:
## Closes DF-18971

## Description
Added GSR LWBA endpoint

## Changes
- Added `crypto-lwba` endpoint as alias to default `price` endpoint with additional aliases `'cryptolwba', and 'crypto_lwba'`
- Added expected LWBA fields to the DP and EA endpoint response bodies in respective `endpoint/` and `transport/` dirs
- Refactored GSR auth code into separate `authutils.ts` file with minor changes to accept multiple sets of configs
- Updated integration tests

<!-- Acceptance testing steps, automated tests should _always_ be included -->

## Steps to Test

1. GSR price endpoint regression (related to refactored authutils)
2. New LWBA endpoint returns expected fields corresponding to DP fields

## Quality Assurance

- [ ] If a new adapter was made, or an existing one was modified so that its environment variables have changed, update the relevant `<ADAPTER_PACKAGE>/schemas/env.json` and `<ADAPTER_PACKAGE>/README.md`
- [ ] If a new adapter was made, or an existing one was modified so that its environment variables have changed, update the relevant `infra-k8s` configuration file.
- [ ] If a new adapter was made, or an existing one was modified so that its environment variables have changed, update the relevant `adapter-secrets` configuration file or update the [soak testing blacklist](/packages/scripts/src/get-changed-adapters/soakTestBlacklist.ts).
- [x] If a new adapter was made, or a new endpoint was added, update the `test-payload.json` file with relevant requests.
- [x] The branch naming follows git flow (`feature/x`, `chore/x`, `release/x`, `hotfix/x`, `fix/x`) or is created from Clubhouse/Shortcut
- [x] This is related to a maximum of one Clubhouse/Shortcut story or GitHub issue
- [x] Types are safe (avoid TypeScript/TSLint features like any and disable, instead use more specific types)
- [x] All code changes have 100% unit and integration test coverage. If testing is not applicable or too difficult to justify doing, the reasoning should be documented explicitly in the PR.

issue.body:
## Closes #DF_19047

## Description
Tiingo EA iex and eod endpoints fail depending on request ordering

## Changes
IEX Endpoint default transport changed to ws

## Steps to Test
yarn test packages/sources/tiingo/test

## Quality Assurance

- [ ] If a new adapter was made, or an existing one was modified so that its environment variables have changed, update the relevant `infra-k8s` configuration file.
- [ ] If a new adapter was made, or an existing one was modified so that its environment variables have changed, update the relevant `adapter-secrets` configuration file or update the [soak testing blacklist](/packages/scripts/src/get-changed-adapters/soakTestBlacklist.ts).
- [ ] If a new adapter was made, or a new endpoint was added, update the `test-payload.json` file with relevant requests.
- [x] The branch naming follows git flow (`feature/x`, `chore/x`, `release/x`, `hotfix/x`, `fix/x`) or is created from Jira.
- [x] This is related to a maximum of one Jira story or GitHub issue.
- [x] Types are safe (avoid TypeScript/TSLint features like any and disable, instead use more specific types).
- [x] All code changes have 100% unit and integration test coverage. If testing is not applicable or too difficult to justify doing, the reasoning should be documented explicitly in the PR.

Tiingo EA iex and eod endpoints fail depending on request ordering

- [x] The branch naming follows git flow (`feature/x`, `chore/x`, `release/x`, `hotfix/x`, `fix/x`) or is created from Jira.
- [x] This is related to a maximum of one Jira story or GitHub issue.

- [x] All code changes have 100% unit and integration test coverage. If testing is not applicable or too difficult to justify doing, the reasoning should be documented explicitly in the PR.

pull_request.body:
## Closes #DF_18875

## Description
Add inverse behaviour to Cryptocompare to support BTC-ETH pair. Since cryptocompare only supports ETH-BTC pair.

## Changes
add Request Transformation for
1. inverse behaviour
2. upper case base and Quote in request

## Steps to Test
yarn test packages/source/cryptocompare

## Quality Assurance

- [ ] If a new adapter was made, or an existing one was modified so that its environment variables have changed, update the relevant `infra-k8s` configuration file.
- [ ] If a new adapter was made, or an existing one was modified so that its environment variables have changed, update the relevant `adapter-secrets` configuration file or update the [soak testing blacklist](/packages/scripts/src/get-changed-adapters/soakTestBlacklist.ts).
- [ ] If a new adapter was made, or a new endpoint was added, update the `test-payload.json` file with relevant requests.
- [x] The branch naming follows git flow (`feature/x`, `chore/x`, `release/x`, `hotfix/x`, `fix/x`) or is created from Jira.
- [x] This is related to a maximum of one Jira story or GitHub issue.
- [x] Types are safe (avoid TypeScript/TSLint features like any and disable, instead use more specific types).
- [x] All code changes have 100% unit and integration test coverage. If testing is not applicable or too difficult to justify doing, the reasoning should be documented explicitly in the PR.
